headline: Palantir Technologies (NasdaqGS:PLTR) Sees 7% Dip Over Last Quarter After Earnings Decline
summary: Palantir Technologies (NasdaqGS:PLTR) recently formed multiple partnerships, such as with Everfox for AI in defense and with Databricks to integrate AI systems. Despite these collaborative efforts and the company's addition to the S&P 100, Palantir's stock saw a 7% decline over the last quarter. This could be attributed to broader market conditions, including a 6% drop in the S&P 500 and a bearish turn for the Nasdaq, partly due to tariff concerns. headline: Palantir Stock Fell Nearly 40% From Its High. History Says This Will Happen Next.
summary: Palantir Technologies (NASDAQ: PLTR) was one of the hottest artificial intelligence (AI) stocks on the market in 2024.  In March, Palantir stock fell nearly 40% from its February high, and the share price is still 33% below that level.  Palantir peaked at $39 per share in early 2021 as investors became overconfident.
